article.headline: Army rolls over Binghamton 80-54
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Kyle Wilson scored 25 points on 9 of 15 shooting and Army rolled over Binghamton 80-54 on Tuesday. The Black Knights (5-0) held Binghamton to just 31.5 percent shooting, including just 4 of 17 from beyond the arc. Army was 9 of 22 from 3-point range (41 percent) and shot 48 percent overall from the floor. Binghamton (1-5) was led by Willie Rodriguez with 20 points and 10 rebounds. Army had a 14-2 run midway through the first half -- including a pair of 3-pointers by Wilson -- and led 38-23 at the break. A similar 13-2 run early in the second half, punctuated by two Luke Morrison treys and another by Wilson, busted the game open for the Black Knights and they marched to an easy win. Army had seven steals and committed just 11 turnovers.
